<node id="EMBEZZLEMENT">
  <data key="d0">EVENT</data>
  <data key="d1">An act of fraud involving the misappropriation of funds entrusted to one's care, specifically public funds within an organization like the Sterling Public Works Department.&lt;SEP&gt;Embezzlement involves misappropriation of public funds entrusted to an individual for a specific purpose without proper authorization or accounting practices.&lt;SEP&gt;Embezzlement is a crime of fraudulently misappropriating funds placed in one's trust.&lt;SEP&gt;Embezzlement is the illegal misuse of funds entrusted to one's care.&lt;SEP&gt;Embezzlement refers to the fraudulent appropriation of funds placed in one's trust.&lt;SEP&gt;Embezzlement refers to the illegal act of misappropriating or stealing public funds entrusted to one's care for personal use, profit-making activities, or when large amounts are stolen and not returned within a specified period.&lt;SEP&gt;The act of fraudulently misappropriating funds entrusted to one's care.&lt;SEP&gt;The act of misappropriating funds from municipal accounts, specifically disaster relief, emergency rescue, and rural development funds.&lt;SEP&gt;The conviction for embezzlement related to misuse of disaster relief and emergency funds.&lt;SEP&gt;The crime of embezzlement committed by V. Martin.&lt;SEP&gt;The crime of fraudulently misappropriating funds entrusted to one's care.</data>
