<node id="C. TAYLOR">
  <data key="d0">PERSON</data>
  <data key="d1">C. Taylor is an individual born on October 19th, 1960, who resides at 71 Yorkshire Street, Unionville and works as a retail shop owner. Throughout her career, she has been involved in various activities related to selling counterfeit goods. In particular, C. Taylor was found guilty of selling counterfeit registered trademark goods and is currently facing charges for selling counterfeit luxury goods in her retail establishment located on 25 Baker Street, Unionville.

The individual's history with selling counterfeit goods includes attempts to dispose of such products upon hearing rumors of an investigation by the Norwood, Unionville Court. C. Taylor has also been involved in promoting counterfeit luxury goods through social media platforms and attempting to sell counterfeit handbags. Additionally, she purchased counterfeit Nike shoes in April 2022.

Throughout her involvement with counterfeit goods, C. Taylor has faced multiple investigations, arrests, and convictions by the Norwood, Unionville Court for selling counterfeit registered trademark goods. As a result of these actions, detention measures were implemented to prevent further illegal activities related to counterfeit goods. The individual is currently informed about her right to appeal within ten days after receiving a court's judgment.

The defendant in Norwood's case involving counterfeit goods is C. Taylor, who has been accused of engaging in deceptive practices regarding counterfeit sales and attempted disposal of counterfeit products upon hearing rumors of an investigation.</data>
