  <data key="d0">EVENT</data>
  <data key="d1">Hepatitis A is a liver disease caused by the hepatitis virus, leading to an intermediate stage of treatment requiring monitoring and supportive care.&lt;SEP&gt;Hepatitis A is a viral infection that causes liver inflammation, characterized by symptoms such as fatigue, loss of appetite, and elevated liver enzymes.&lt;SEP&gt;Hepatitis A is a viral infection that leads to conditions such as hepatomegaly, necessitating medical intervention like abdominal drainage.&lt;SEP&gt;Hepatitis A is a viral liver infection that can be transmitted through contaminated food or water.&lt;SEP&gt;Hepatitis A is a viral liver infection that can be transmitted through the fecal-oral route, often resulting from contaminated food or water.&lt;SEP&gt;Hepatitis A is a viral liver infection that can cause symptoms such as jaundice and elevated liver enzymes.&lt;SEP&gt;Hepatitis A is an infectious disease caused by the Hepatitis A virus, leading to liver inflammation.&lt;SEP&gt;Hepatitis A is an infectious disease with symptoms such as fatigue, loss of appetite, enlarged liver, and abnormal liver function.</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ac8911078a04dccfe21e76745d57a87e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-16068ec8099bfd0c973ce77d2e31e98e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f989005aa3678ee4a849493717587db7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c4252f9864c5e8a91e41e51061c98573&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-78f3954603d0866c182e2c0b02d6b3c7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0be8304c3ca3535143e259804fbf2912&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-908080bcc53f03112ee21fd7fbf57367&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c67cadbd661328238eba8e5805a54839</data>
