<node id="MASTOIDITIS">
  <data key="d0">EVENT</data>
  <data key="d1">A bacterial infection affecting the mastoid process of the temporal bone, often causing pain and swelling.&lt;SEP&gt;Inflammation of the mastoid bone, a condition that may require medical treatment and careful management.&lt;SEP&gt;Mastitis is an inflammation of the mastoid bone in the temporal region, often associated with purulence.&lt;SEP&gt;Mastoiditis is an infection of the mastoid bone behind the ear, often causing severe pain and swelling.&lt;SEP&gt;Mastoiditis is an infection of the mastoid bone in the temporal region, characterized by redness, swelling, purulent discharge in the external auditory canal, and opacification/inflammation visible on CT scan.&lt;SEP&gt;Mastoiditis is an infection of the mastoid bone in the temporal region, often treated at hospitals like Cameron General Hospital.&lt;SEP&gt;Mastoiditis is an infection of the mastoid process in the temporal bone of the skull.</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-87109323321cdb1a506a74f98c09ff68&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-daaee7a3822ca075f0b4c323cd473bd4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0afbba3aeda43d5bc02b9db6fdb0078&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1848bb8740d8273223bf693db78b66fe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f26c9f3a0232fb670b36552112fe20d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9787cfe00a9dca18879ace7693cbbd0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5ff2c0697d8cf9d494fd52625b78a313</data>
</node>
