<node id="PARKINSON'S DISEASE">
  <data key="d0">EVENT</data>
  <data key="d1">A neurological condition that affects movement and causes tremors, stiffness, and difficulty with balance and coordination.&lt;SEP&gt;A progressive neurological disorder characterized by tremors, rigidity, and bradykinesia.&lt;SEP&gt;Parkinson's Disease is a neurological condition that affects movement and coordination, requiring ongoing management and treatment.&lt;SEP&gt;Parkinson's Disease is a progressive neurological disorder affecting movement and causing motor symptoms such as tremor, bradykinesia, rigidity, and postural instability.&lt;SEP&gt;Parkinson's Disease is a progressive neurological disorder characterized by motor and non-motor symptoms.&lt;SEP&gt;Parkinson's Disease is a progressive neurological disorder characterized by motor symptoms such as tremors, rigidity, slow movement, and postural instability, along with non-motor symptoms like constipation, olfactory disorders, sleep disorders, autonomic dysfunction, and cognitive impairments.&lt;SEP&gt;Parkinson's Disease is a progressive neurological disorder characterized by tremors, bradykinesia, rigidity, and postural instability.</data>
