<node id="CONGENITAL HEART DISEASE">
  <data key="d0">EVENT</data>
  <data key="d1">A condition where there are structural problems in the heart present from birth.&lt;SEP&gt;A group of heart conditions present from birth, affecting the structure of the heart. One specific type mentioned is Ventricular Septal Defect.&lt;SEP&gt;Congenital Heart Disease is a condition that affects the structure of the heart and its ability to function properly, often leading to symptoms such as repeated respiratory infections, palpitations, shortness of breath, and cyanosis.&lt;SEP&gt;Congenital heart disease is a condition that affects the heart from birth, requiring careful management and monitoring.&lt;SEP&gt;Congenital heart disease refers to a condition in which the heart's structures, such as chambers and valves, are not fully developed before birth.</data>
